body:
![mis-behaving-tree-painting](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1533520/61252158-79b99980-a711-11e9-9034-449db5909a52.png)


It is possible to have the widget tree drawings in the editor misbehave by adding and  removing the `new` keyword.  In the screenshot adding and removing `new` before the `Expanded` widget adds and removes the tree lines in the editor.

comment_data.body: Do you have a repro project? That is a bug. It looks like the outline view is fine so the bug is probably in the logic rendering the ui guides from the outline view.
Best information for a repo is the LHS of the screenshot.  I typed out these widgets in one session.  Latest Flutter version and Flutter IJ versions
@helin24 Is this fixed? If not, could you add the `bug` label?
This seems to no longer be an issue, in DevTools or in the Java inspector.
